            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-03-23T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-03-23T21:00:00-05:00" n="941" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d941">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.6363/3–2449: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-03-24T10:00:00+08:00">March 24, 1949—10 a. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received March 23—10:49 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>982. ConGen told first feeler negotiate 20,000 drums kerosene delivery Tientsin
                    received unidentified Communist go-between Shanghai and referred home offices
                    Standard-Vacuum, Texas, Shell.</p>
                <p>ConGen orally asking local oil companies for information this subject as details
                    become available to coordinate information Communist trade policy toward foreign
                    firms.</p>
                <p>Would appreciate Department’s views such transactions in view substantial amount
                    involved and category of oil sought.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 982; repeated Nanking 578.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
